# 🗺️ Google Maps + Chrome Extension Workflow

This workflow represents a **Hybrid Method** for lead generation. Instead of using a paid direct API (like Outscraper), you use a Chrome Extension to manually find leads on Google Maps and then import them into your CRM for AI processing.

## 📊 Workflow Flowchart

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Step 1: Manual Discovery
    Start((Start)) --> Search[Search Niche on Google Maps<br/>'e.g. Software Company in Noida']
    Search --> Scroll[Scroll through results<br/>to load data]
    
    %% Step 2: Extraction
    Scroll --> Extension[Launch Chrome Extension<br/>'e.g. Instant Data Scraper']
    Extension --> Export[Export Data to CSV/Excel]
    
    %% Step 3: Integration
    Export --> Import[Upload CSV to CRM<br/>'Leads > Import' Button]
    Import --> Parse[CRM Logic Parses CSV<br/>Matches columns like Name, Phone, Site]
    
    %% Step 4: CRM Enrichment (The Real Work)
    Parse --> DB[(PostgreSQL Database)]
    DB --> LinkFinder[CRM Searches LinkedIn<br/>Finds CEO/Founder via Search Index]
    LinkFinder --> AIEngine[AI Personalization<br/>Generates customized msg per CEO]
    
    %% Step 5: Outreach
    AIEngine --> Send[Send Outreach<br/>via LinkedIn or Email]
    Send --> FollowUp[Automated Follow-up Worker]
    FollowUp --> Close((Deal Closed))

    %% Styling
    style Start fill:#f9f,stroke:#333
    style Close fill:#00ff00,stroke:#333
    style Extension fill:#f96,stroke:#333
    style AIEngine fill:#4f46e5,stroke:#fff
```

